-- Hypermarcas Says Profit Fell 41% in 4th Quarter on Acquisitions
-- B y   S t e p h a n   N i e l s e n
-- 2012-03-10T18:12:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-10/hypermarcas-says-profit-fell-41-in-4th-quarter-on-acquisitions.html
Hypermarcas SA (HYPE3) , the Brazilian
consumer-products company, said its fourth-quarter profit fell
41 percent as it worked to integrate acquisitions made the past
two years.  Net income fell to 49.6 million reais ($27.7 million) in
the fourth quarter from 84.1 million reais in the year-ago
period, the Sao Paulo-based company said in a  filing .  Revenue rose 1.3 percent to 841.8 million reais.  Hypermarcas, the maker of Pielus shampoo and Episol
sunscreen lotion, has taken on debt to make at least 12
acquisitions since the start of 2010. They include drugmaker
Mantecorp Industria Quimica & Farmaceutica SA and diaper-maker
Sapeka - Industria e Comercio de Fraldas Descartaveis Ltda. Net
debt rose 56 percent to 2.74 billion reais in the quarter from
the year-ago period.  Shares fell 3.94 percent to 11.45 reais yesterday in Sao
Paulo trading. The stock is up 3 percent year to date.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Stephan Nielsen in Sao Paulo at 
 snielsen8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net . 